## Non-Negotiable Constraints

> These constraints are duplicated from `.github/copilot-instructions.md` because CLAUDE.md may be the only framework file Claude reads in some configurations. These are not optional and cannot be overridden by any agent, skill, or user request.

1. **No AI-generated UI** — All designs manually crafted, `{{CSS_FRAMEWORK}}` base. *(Rationale: AI-generated UI skips human review of accessibility and visual correctness, producing components that may fail WCAG 2.1 AA before any oversight can catch them.)*
2. **No copy-paste code** — Extract to utilities; use the DRY principle.
3. **No abandoned PRs** — Features ship or get reverted; no perpetual draft PRs.
4. **No secrets in logs** — Mask tokens/passwords; sanitize error messages.
5. **Core stack is locked** — `{{SERVER_FRAMEWORK}}`, `{{FRONTEND_FRAMEWORK}}`, `{{DATABASE}}`, `{{ORM}}`, `{{CONTAINER_RUNTIME}}`. Changes require an ADR.
6. **Scripts live under `{{SCRIPTS_DIR}}/`** — No operational scripts at repository root.
7. **Command-first execution only** — Use `{{TASK_RUNNER}} <target>` instead of invoking scripts directly.
8. **Skills must be flat files** — Each skill is `.github/skills/<skill_name>.md`; no per-skill subfolders.
9. **No false-complete claims** — Do not say work is done unless the user-visible path is verified, the app is reachable, and required verification passes — or the blocking issue is explicitly surfaced.
10. **No broken handoff** — If a change breaks the app, continue working until service is restored and verification passes. Never stop at "implemented" while the app is non-functional.
11. **No operator setup docs in tracked folders** — Provider walkthroughs, API key steps, and per-tenant config live in `docs/local/` (gitignored). `.env.example` is the only tracked record of which env vars exist.

